pd_0_com_0text: I've got the cards. How do we play?
pd_1_com_0text: Just a simple game of Shtoss.
pd_1_com_1text: You remember how to play Shtoss, correct?
pd_2_com_0text: You wound me. Everybody remembers how to play Shtoss.
pd_2_com_1text: I can't seem to remember. Can you remind me?
pd_4_com_0text: One game, the winner takes it all. Seems easy enough.
pd_5_com_0text: That would make it far less interesting. How about playing three times?
pd_6_com_0text: I haven't realized you enjoyed my company so much.
pd_7_com_0text: Don't flatter yourself. Are you in or not?
pd_8_com_0text: Quite the contrary. I'm looking out for you.
pd_9_com_0text: For me? You must be our of your mind.
pd_11_com_0text: Alright, I'll bite. Three games it is.
pd_12_com_0text: What did you say your name was again?
pd_16_com_0text: Not going to ask about my name?
pd_18_com_1text: I wouldn't tell you even if I did.
pd_20_com_0text: You seem very good at this game.
pd_21_com_0text: I have a gift for cards.
pd_22_com_1text: That makes you sound like a douche.
pd_23_com_0text: Not when you are betting your freedom on it.
pd_25_com_0text: That makes me win like a douche, too.
pd_27_com_0text: Ah, you are making the same mistake again.
pd_28_com_0text: Oh really. Have we played before?
pd_28_com_1text: Must be nice, playing against an amnesiac.
pd_29_com_0text: I suppose there is no harm in telling you.
pd_29_com_1text: Yes, this isn't our first game together.
pd_30_com_0text: I don't recall those games at all. That seems unfair.
pd_31_com_0text: You are quite capable, for an amnesiac.
pd_32_com_0text: Definitely does not feel like it.
pd_33_com_0text: Do you want to just let me have this win?
pd_35_com_0text: Because my memories are gone and you feel sorry for me?
pd_35_com_1text: Because my eyes are blue like the ocean and you are lost at sea?
pd_36_com_0text: I feel sorry for me having to deal with your antics.
pd_37_com_0text: Your eyes are like the deepest pits of hell and I'm taking this win.
pd_38_com_0text: Well, that was worth a try.
pd_41_com_0text: Would you look at that? Lady Luck is on my side today.
pd_41_com_1text: Looks like I'm taking the first win.
pd_43_com_1text: So much for a little faith.
pd_45_com_0text: It was an honest win. Don't be upset.
pd_46_com_0text: I don't trust your kind. Where is the ace of spades? I haven't seen it for an entire game.
pd_48_com_0text: Nonsense. Why didn't I get it in my hand?
pd_49_com_0text: Because we didn't go through the whole deck? Just relax.
pd_50_com_0text: Do not tell me what to do.
pd_50_com_1text: Celebrate this win for as long as you can because you will be destroyed next game.
pd_51_com_0text: You are so dramatic. Do you perhaps own a theatre?
pd_51_com_1text: Whatever helps you sleep at night.
pd_55_com_0text: Phew. That was intense. But this must be a good sign.
pd_56_com_0text: I won the first game. One more win, and I'll be free.
pd_59_com_0text: The ace of spades is indeed not in the deck. I should look for it.
pd_60_com_0text: I take it even more suspicious names were taken?
pd_60_com_1text: Daemon? Sounds so douchey. I'm going to call you Douchemon.
pd_63_com_0text: The amnesia must have really gotten to you.
pd_63_com_1text: It's a simple game, really. We start with five cards each.
pd_63_com_2text: The higher the value, the more powerful the card is, with the ace of spades being the highest card.
pd_63_com_3text: It is easier to explain when we start playing.
pd_63_com_4text: You'll pick it up as we go.
pd_64_com_0text: So eager to start playing against someone who does not know the rules.
pd_66_com_0text: Alright, we can figure it out as we go.
pd_67_com_1text: How exactly are we playing? I have the cards, and you are literally in a portrait.
pd_70_com_0text: Nothing. It's just amusing that I have to explain this to you.
pd_70_com_1text: The cards are from a different dimension. They transcend time and space because they have no real home.
pd_71_com_0text: No real home. That sounds almost sad.
pd_71_com_1text: How did you come to be in posession of such an artifact again?
pd_75_com_0text: I have to know what home feels like to miss it.
